  "text": "The LLVM IR-to-Machine-Code generation pipeline is implemented across several key components in the github.com/llvm/llvm-project repository:\n\n1. **SelectionDAGISel (Instruction Selection)**: Defined in `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h`, this is the common base class used for SelectionDAG-based pattern-matching instruction selectors. It converts LLVM IR into target-specific SelectionDAG nodes. The implementation is in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGISel.cpp`.\n\n2. **SelectionDAGBuilder (IR to DAG Translation)**: Defined in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h`, this is the common target-independent lowering implementation that is parameterized by a TargetLowering object. It translates LLVM IR instructions into SelectionDAG nodes. The implementation is in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.cpp`.\n\n3. **ScheduleDAGRRList (Instruction Scheduling)**: Implemented in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp`, this class is the actual register reduction list scheduler implementation. It supports both top-down and bottom-up scheduling of SelectionDAG nodes and has subclasses handling priority-based scheduling.\n\n4. **RAGreedy (Register Allocation)**: Defined in `llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h`, the RAGreedy class is the greedy register allocator that performs register allocation on the machine function. It extends RegAllocBase and handles allocation of virtual registers to physical registers with eviction-based strategies.\n\n5. **MachineFunction (Machine-Level Function Representation)**: Defined in `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h`, this is the core data structure representing a function at the machine code level. It contains a list of MachineBasicBlock instances and pointers to various classes holding target-specific information about the generated code. This is the primary data structure that flows through all stages of the code generation pipeline.\n\nThese five components form the essential stages of the LLVM code generation pipeline: IR lowering to SelectionDAG, instruction selection, scheduling, register allocation, and final machine code representation."
}

